12/12/2006
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Croatia opened and provisionally closed negotiations Monday (December 11th) with the EU on the Education and Culture chapter of the acquis.
There are 31 chapters remaining.
On Tuesday, EU foreign ministers meeting in Brussels praised Croatia for the achieved progress in the past year, but urged the country to step up efforts to combat corruption, among other things.
(Vecernji list, Vjesnik - 12/12/06;
HRT, HINA, EU website - 11/12/06)
